    {
      "title": "Form VII Verbs (اِنْفَعَلَ)",
      "titleArabic": "باب اِنْفَعَلَ",
      "content": [
        "Form VII verbs are formed by prefixing اِنْ to the root. This pattern typically indicates a passive or reflexive meaning, showing that something happens to the subject rather than the subject doing it."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Pattern: اِنْفَعَلَ (infa'ala) - prefix in to root",
        "Maṣdar pattern: اِنْفِعَال (infi'āl)",
        "Mostly intransitive verbs",
        "Shows result of an action: كَسَرَ (to break) → اِنْكَسَرَ (to become broken)"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "اِنْكَسَرَ", "english": "to break (intransitive)" },
        { "arabic": "اِنْفَتَحَ", "english": "to open (by itself)" },
        { "arabic": "اِنْتَشَرَ", "english": "to spread" }
      ]
    }
